    "body": "We are currently able to [use a multi-threaded shuffle writer](https://github.com/NVIDIA/spark-rapids/blob/branch-22.12/sql-plugin/src/main/scala/org/apache/spark/sql/rapids/RapidsShuffleInternalManagerBase.scala#L1185) when Spark would have used the `BypassMergeSortShuffleWriter`.\r\n\r\nThere are similar issues with CPU-bound work for compression that can be seen in traces for [UnsafeShuffleWriter](https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/master/core/src/main/java/org/apache/spark/shuffle/sort/UnsafeShuffleWriter.java#L67) \r\n\r\nThis task is to research if the multi-threaded approach for compression/serialization makes sense here. It seems like it should given that compression and serialization are still single threaded, and happening in the task thread.",
